div.span: Admins have access to devices within their organisation that allows them to view temperature readings of their own devices and users. They have the ability to remotely set devices into QR mode, or receive email notifications. Within this group there are super admins which have the ability to add and modify new devices, as well as add new users. These users are set within Cognito pool manually by adding them to the admin group.

The back end that runs on the raspberry pi includes a number of services/components, listed are the services used directly in recording temperatures. There are a number of other services around updating/versioning. It is primarily written in Go, and interfaces with the thermal camera and the web interface providing frames through a web socket.
Related Links: https://github.com/feverscreen/feverscreen
